{"title": "Cicero and the Fall of the Roman Republic", "description": "\"The purpose of this volume is to tell the story of Cicero's life, and at the same time to set forth from his writings a presentation of the concluding age of the Roman Republic, and to record the disastrous but not inglorious failure of the last Free State of the ancient world.  So far as may be, I propose to let Cicero himself to speak to my readers.\"  ", "duration": 41829, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "19390", "name": "James Leigh Strachan-Davidson"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/cicero_2603_librivox/cicero_2603.jpg", "copyright_year": "1903", "genres": ["Biography & Autobiography", "Political Science"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Lynette Caulkins"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/cicero_2603_librivox/cicero_00_strachandavidson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 113}, {"section": 1, "title": "Cicero's Training", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/cicero_2603_librivox/cicero_01_strachandavidson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2396}, {"section": 2, "title": "Roman Parties and Statesmen", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/cicero_2603_librivox/cicero_02_strachandavidson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2744}, {"section": 3, "title": "Cicero as an Advocate; Atticus; Cicero's Family", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/cicero_2603_librivox/cicero_03_strachandavidson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2893}, {"section": 4, "title": "Cicero as a Magistrate", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/cicero_2603_librivox/cicero_04_strachandavidson_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2764}, {"section": 5, "title": "Cicero and Cataline", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.o